Do me the favor to accept the accompanying little book.<note><hi rend="italic">The Chimes</hi>. This letter accompanied a presentation copy, inscribed "Mrs: Curry | From | Charles Dickens | Genoa. Twelfth April 1845".</note> It is a very poor mark of my sincere and cordial regard; but I would live in your recollection sometimes after leaving here: and it may serve, perhaps, as a help to your remembrance, for want of a better.
